<h2>Santa Ana Winds — Yorba Linda Specific Maintenance</h2>
<p>Yorba Linda sits in inland OC where Santa Ana wind events hit directly from the east. October through December brings dry, hot winds gusting 40–60mph in strong events. These winds affect LG dryers in Yorba Linda in two specific ways:</p>
<p><strong>Debris in vent caps.</strong> Santa Ana winds carry dry leaves, dust, and debris that enters exterior vent caps during high-wind events. A cap that's clean before a Santa Ana can be 30–40% restricted after a single overnight event in an exposed Yorba Linda location. Elevated neighbourhoods like Blackhorse Canyon, Hidden Hills, and the Country Club area are most affected. We recommend checking exterior cap condition after every major Santa Ana event — and September vent cleaning as the optimal annual timing, before the wind season arrives.</p>
<p><strong>Pressure reversal in vent systems.</strong> Strong Santa Ana events can create brief positive pressure at exterior vent caps — pushing air back into the vent from outside. This redistributes loose lint from duct walls further into the system. A vent managing fine before a Santa Ana event may show d80 restriction codes afterward. If your LG shows d80 in October or November after a wind event, the vent cap and duct should be checked before assuming the machine has a problem.</p>

